<text id="F1108T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>H.W. Freedley tells Maria Hiester about his severe leg wound. His handwriting is shaky.</p> 
</div1> 
</front> 

<body id="d4">
<div1 type="letter" id="d5">


<opener>
<dateline>
<date value="1863-07-29">July 29<hi rend="super"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> 1863</date> 
    <name type="place">Gettysburg, <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">Pen</abbr></name> 
</dateline> 
<salute>Dear Maria</salute> 
</opener> 

<p>This is the first letter I have written for I thought that it would be strange to dictate to your father a letter <del hand="h1">from</del> for him to write to his daughter</p>
<p>I am glad to hear that you are all so well Your father never looked so well</p>
<p>Maria I am seriously <unclear>sadly</unclear> <add hand="h1" place="inline">wounded</add> I will not be able to be moved from here <orig reg="within">with in</orig> a month,<pb n="2"/></p>
<p>I will not write to you again. You little know the pain much exertion <unclear>it</unclear> cost You shall <add hand="h1" place="inline">hear</add> promptly of every change in the state of my wound through your father.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Ever Affectionately</salute> 
<signed>HW Freedley</signed> 
</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
